.TH "message_store" 9 "message_store" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
message_store \- write a new message via sysfs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" message_store
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the LCD device
.IP "attr" 12
the LCD message attribute
.IP "buf" 12
the buffer containing the new message
.IP "count" 12
the size of the message in \fIbuf\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Write a new message to display or scroll across the LCD display from sysfs.
.SH "RETURN"
the size of the message on success, else -ERRNO
